<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870423-0184 </DOCNO><HL> Dividend News:Potomac Electric Power Co.</HL><DD> 04/23/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> POMDIVIDENDS (DIV) </IN><TEXT>   POTOMAC ELECTRIC POWER CO. declared a 2-for-1 stock split payable May 18 to stock of record May 4. The Washington, D.C., utility, which has 47.2 million shares outstanding, declared a quarterly dividend of 32.5 cents a share on a post-split basis payable June 30 to stock of record June 2. Holders at the annual meeting approved boosting authorized shares to 200 million from 80 million; staggering terms for directors; requiring a prospective purchaser to pay all holders the same price in a hostile takeover bid, and setting &quot;minimum price&quot; criteria for such a bid. </TEXT></DOC>